] glorified in the early medieval ''[[Tevaram]]'' poems by Tamil [[Saivite]] [[Nayanars|Nayanar]] [[Tirugnanasambandar]].<ref name=\"dm\"/> [[Tirumeeyachur Ilamkovil Sakalabhuvaneswarar Temple]] is also found in this temple premises.\n\n== Literary mention ==\n[[File:Lalithambigai2.jpg|200x200px|left|Image of Kshetra Puraneswarar|thumb]]\nTirugnanasambandar describes the feature of the deity as:<ref>Tirugnanasambandar Tevaram, II: 62:7</ref> \n{{cquote|\u0ba8\u0bc0\u0bb2 \u0bb5\u0b9f\u0bbf\u0bb5\u0bb0\u0bcd \u0bae\u0bbf\u0b9f\u0bb1\u0bc1 \u0ba8\u0bc6\u0b9f\u0bbf\u0baf\u0bb0\u0bcd \u0ba8\u0bbf\u0b95\u0bb0\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bcd\u0bb2\u0bbe\u0bb0\u0bcd<br>\n\u0b95\u0bcb\u0bb2 \u0bb5\u0b9f\u0bbf\u0bb5\u0bc1 \u0ba4\u0bae\u0ba4\u0bbe\u0b99\u0bcd \u0b95\u0bca\u0bb3\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc8 \u0baf\u0bb1\u0bbf\u0bb5\u0bca\u0ba3\u0bcd\u0ba3\u0bbe\u0bb0\u0bcd<br>\n\u0b95\u0bbe\u0bb2\u0bb0\u0bcd \u0b95\u0bb4\u0bb2\u0bb0\u0bcd \u0b95\u0bb0\u0bbf\u0baf\u0bbf \u0ba9\u0bc1\u0bb0\u0bbf\u0baf\u0bb0\u0bcd \u0bae\u0bb4\u0bc1\u0bb5\u0bbe\u0bb3\u0bb0\u0bcd<br>\n\u0bae\u0bc7\u0bb2\u0bb0\u0bcd \u0bae\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0baf\u0bb0\u0bcd \u0bb5\u0bbf\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0baf\u0bb0\u0bcd \u0bae\u0bc0\u0baf\u0b9a\u0bcd \u0b9a\u0bc2\u0bb0\u0bbe\u0bb0\u0bc7.}}\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{cite web|title= Sri Mehanadhar temple|url= http://temple.dinamalar.com/en/new_en.php?id=599 |publisher =[[Dinamalar]]}}\n* {{cite web|title= Muyarchinatheswarar Temple, Tirumeeyachur\n |url= http://www.shivatemples.com/sofc/sc056.php |publisher=Shiva Temples of Tamilnadu, Paadal Petra Sivasthalangal}}\n\n==\u0baa\u0b9f\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bca\u0b95\u0bc1\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bc1==\n<center>\n<gallery>\nTirumiyachur meganathar temple3.jpg|Rajagopuram\nTirumiyachur meganathar temple4.jpg|Flagpost\nTirumiyachur meganathar temple5.jpg|Front mandapa\nTirumiyachur meganathar temple6.jpg|Vimana of the presiding deity\nTirumiyachur meganathar temple7.jpg|Mehanadhar vimana and Sakalabhuvanesvarar vimana\nTirumiyachur meganathar temple8.jpg|Vimana from north side\n</gallery>\n</center>\n\n[[Category:Shiva temples in Tiruvarur district]]\n[[Category:Padal Petra Stalam]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox Hindu temple\n| name               = Mehanadhar Temple\n| image              = Lalithambigai1.jpg\n| alt          = \n| caption            = \n| map_type        = India Tamil Nadu\n| map_caption        = Location in Tamil Nadu\n| coordinates        = {{coord|10|57|46|N|79|38|50|E|type:landmark_region:IN|display=inline,title}}\n| native_name        = Lalithambika temple\n| country            = [[India]]\n| state              = [[Tamil Nadu]]\n| district           = [[Tiruvarur district|Thiruvarur]]\n| location           = Tirumeichur\n| elevation_m        = \n| deity  = Mehanathar ([[Shiva]])\nLalithambika ([[Parvathi]])\n \n \n| facade_direction = \n| temple_tank        = \n| tower              = \n| festivals= \n| architecture       = [[Dravidian architecture]]\n| temple_quantity  = \n| monument_quantity= \n| inscriptions       = \n| year_completed         = \n| creator            = \n| website            = \n}}\n'''Tirumeeyachur Mehanadhar Temple'''<ref name=\"dinamalar\">{{Cite web\n|url= http://temple.dinamalar.com/en/new_en.php?id=599\n|title= Sri Mehanadhar temple|work=Dinamalar temples\n|accessdate=8 August 2015\n}}</ref>\n(\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0bb0\u0bc1\u0bae\u0bc0\u0baf\u0b9a\u0bcd\u0b9a\u0bc2\u0bb0\u0bcd \u0bae\u0bc7\u0b95\u0ba8\u0bbe\u0ba4\u0bb0\u0bcd \u0b95\u0bcb\u0baf\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bcd) is a [[Hindu temple]] located at Thirumeeyachur in [[Tiruvarur district]], [[Tamil Nadu]], [[India]].<ref>[http://www.shivatemples.com/sofc/sc056.php Muyarchinatheswarar Temple, Tirumeeyachur]</ref> The presiding deity is [[Shiva]]. He is called as Meganathaswami. His consort is known as Lalithambika.<ref name=\"dm\">[http://temple.dinamalar.com/en/new_en.php?id=599 Sri Mehanadhar temple]</ref>\n\n== Significance ==\n[[File:Lalithambigai3.jpg|200x200px|left|Image of temple towers|thumb]]\nIt is one of the shrines of the 275 [[Paadal Petra Sthalams]] - [[Shiva Temples of Tamil Nadu#Sthalams|Shiva Sthalams]] glorified in the early medieval ''[[Tevaram]]'' poems by Tamil [[Saivite]] [[Nayanars|Nayanar]] [[Tirugnanasambandar]].<ref name=\"dm\"/> [[Tirumeeyachur Ilamkovil Sakalabhuvaneswarar Temple]] is also found in this temple premises.\n\n== Literary Mention ==\n[[File:Lalithambigai2.jpg|200x200px|left|Image of Kshetra Puraneswarar|thumb]]\nTirugnanasambandar describes the feature of the deity as:<ref>Tirugnanasambandar Tevaram, II: 62:7</ref> \n{{cquote|\u0ba8\u0bc0\u0bb2 \u0bb5\u0b9f\u0bbf\u0bb5\u0bb0\u0bcd \u0bae\u0bbf\u0b9f\u0bb1\u0bc1 \u0ba8\u0bc6\u0b9f\u0bbf\u0baf\u0bb0\u0bcd \u0ba8\u0bbf\u0b95\u0bb0\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bcd\u0bb2\u0bbe\u0bb0\u0bcd<br>\n\u0b95\u0bcb\u0bb2 \u0bb5\u0b9f\u0bbf\u0bb5\u0bc1 \u0ba4\u0bae\u0ba4\u0bbe\u0b99\u0bcd \u0b95\u0bca\u0bb3\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc8 \u0baf\u0bb1\u0bbf\u0bb5\u0bca\u0ba3\u0bcd\u0ba3\u0bbe\u0bb0\u0bcd<br>\n\u0b95\u0bbe\u0bb2\u0bb0\u0bcd \u0b95\u0bb4\u0bb2\u0bb0\u0bcd \u0b95\u0bb0\u0bbf\u0baf\u0bbf \u0ba9\u0bc1\u0bb0\u0bbf\u0baf\u0bb0\u0bcd \u0bae\u0bb4\u0bc1\u0bb5\u0bbe\u0bb3\u0bb0\u0bcd<br>\n\u0bae\u0bc7\u0bb2\u0bb0\u0bcd \u0bae\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0baf\u0bb0\u0bcd \u0bb5\u0bbf\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0baf\u0bb0\u0bcd \u0bae\u0bc0\u0baf\u0b9a\u0bcd \u0b9a\u0bc2\u0bb0\u0bbe\u0bb0\u0bc7.}}\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{cite web|title= Sri Mehanadhar temple|url= http://temple.dinamalar.com/en/new_en.php?id=599 |publisher =[[Dinamalar]]}}\n* {{cite web|title= Muyarchinatheswarar Temple, Tirumeeyachur\n |url= http://www.shivatemples.com/sofc/sc056.php |publisher=Shiva Temples of Tamilnadu, Paadal Petra Sivasthalangal}}\n\n==\u0baa\u0b9f\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bca\u0b95\u0bc1\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bc1==\n<center>\n<gallery>\nTirumiyachur meganathar temple3.jpg|Rajagopuram\nTirumiyachur meganathar temple4.jpg|Flagpost\nTirumiyachur meganathar temple5.jpg|Front mandapa\nTirumiyachur meganathar temple6.jpg|Vimana of the presiding deity\nTirumiyachur meganathar temple7.jpg|Mehanadhar vimana and Sakalabhuvanesvarar vimana\nTirumiyachur meganathar temple8.jpg|Vimana from north side\n</gallery>\n</center>\n\n[[Category:Shiva temples in Tiruvarur district]]\n[[Category:Padal Petra Stalam]]\n", "name_user": "Titodutta", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eLiterary mention:clean up,MOS:HEADCAPS", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tirumeeyachur_Mehanadhar_Temple"}
